node.text:
Hey guys, I need your help finding people deserving of a pick me up. I’ve been blessed to have gathered up so much fishing gear over a 10 year professional career and I’ve come to realize there’s no way I could possibly use all of it. 

So I’ve gathered up at least $20,000 USD of my gear, fishing rods, reels, tackle, etc, to give away. Nominate someone you know who could use some gear and my team is going to help go through all the comments and pick people to send some stuff to. Use the hash tag #JWGrassrootsGiveback in your reply or a new post to make sure we see it! Thanks!

node.text: A lot of things played into ultimately taking home the W this week. You all know some of the key baits, the flogger and the beefed up tackle to get those smallmouth in faster, but the biggest unsung hero of the week for me was my @wileyx Omega sunglasses with the Captivate lens. Without that piece of the puzzle this weeks game plan wouldn’t have been possible. Seriously ever since I’ve started using the Captivate lens in my frames I see so much more detail. That was a huge deal this week in picking out subtle differences and finding the fish that were a little deeper than most people were looking. Big shoutout to @wileyx for making such a great product! Thank you all. 👊🏼

node.text: What a week!! I truly don’t know where to start. This event was an absolute battle and probably one of the toughest events I’ve fished on my body. Having my family here is such a big a deal to me and being able to share this with them is something I will never forget. I’ve learned to take a minute and step back to enjoy the moment because ultimately you don’t know when your next one will be. Thinking just 10 years ago fishing professionally was only a dream to me at that point is something that is really unbelievable to think about.  I say this because I know a lot of people out there are in the crossroads of their life and I want this to encourage you to chase your dreams. We are only given one life so work hard and get out there and make it happen! Thank you all for your continued support! At heart I’m still just that young kid from Indy looking for his next bite.  @academy @magellanoutdoors
